  "headline": "A 43-minute loss decided on the map — towers 6–11 and you bled every late Prime (27, 33, 38) to them. The long game slipped away, not the draft.",
  "team": "You actually traded the early Fangtooths evenly, but from 25 minutes on they took every Prime and out-towered you 11–6. That's a closing/teamfight problem, not an itemization one — anti-heal was covered (2 vs a single healer). Three players sat on a bottom-two lane (Mr_Meat support, Cuban mid, Willy offlane), which made the solo lanes a slog. Win the late-game setpieces or end before them.",
  "whatShiftedIt": "Group for the 25-minute+ Primes as a five — that's where the towers and the game went. Tighten the lineup so your solo lanes aren't uphill.",
  "perPlayer": {
   "7c8ab99c-31c5-4ea5-a6fa-e0d6417c3f1b": "Adele into Mourn (1/10) — support is a bottom-two lane for you; offlane is your seat. Ten deaths on a backline enchanter is the game in one stat.",
   "16f28434-561f-4f23-9454-40321f4a1ef3": "Legion 13/5 carried the scoreboard on a low-sample hero — fine pick, it worked; the loss was the team's late map, not your lane.",
